==English==
===Etymology===
From ''[[beg]]'' + ''[[-ar]]''

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɛɡə(r)|-ɛɡə(r)]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
#A person who [[beg|begs]].
#A person suffering from extreme [[poverty]].
#*'''1883:''' [[w:Robert Louis Stevenson|Robert Louis Stevenson]], ''[[w:Treasure Island|Treasure Island]]''
#*: I'm to be a poor, crawling '''beggar''', sponging for rum, when I might be rolling in a coach!

====Translations====
{{top}}
*Dutch: [[bedelaar]].  As "Beggar" it is also used for "Geus" and as "Sea Beggar" for "Watergeus" (see translation in French for etymology)
*French: [[mendiant]] ''m'' , [[gueux]] ''m''
*[[Greek]]: [[ζητιάνα]] ''f''
*Norwegian: [[tigger]] ''m''
*Telugu: [[బిచ్చగాడు]] (bichchagaaDu) {{m}}, [[బిచ్చగత్తె]] (bichchagatte) {{f}}
